quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  97,1,"We sent it1down on the Night of Determination."
  97,2,"But what can make yousg realize what the Night of Determination is?"
  97,3,"The Night of Determination is better than a thousand months—"
  97,4,"in it descend the angels, with the Spirit1among them, by the leave of their Lord with every command."
  97,5,"Peace! It is until the rise1 of dawn."
  98,1,"Those who have denied from among the People of the Scripture and the polytheists were not to be parted(from disbelief) until the evident proof came to them—"
  98,2,"a messenger from Allah reading purified Scrolls;"
  98,3,"in them are valuable scriptures."
  98,4,"Nor did those who were given the Scripture become divided except after the evident proof came to them."
  98,5,"And they were only commanded to worship Allah—devoting religion to Him, turning away from all that is false—and to establish the prayer and to bring1the purifying charity2, and that is the religion3most upright."
  98,6,"Indeed, those who have denied among the People of the Scripture and the polytheists are in the fire of Hell, abiding therein; those are the worst of all beings."
  98,7,"Indeed, those who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds—those are the best of all beings."